---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="Stokvel Society" description="A fintech product designed around contribution clarity, ledger trust, and payout visibility.">
  <section class="page-section">
    <div class="container page-hero-layout">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div class="page-intro">Community finance</div>
        <h1 class="page-title">Stokvel Society</h1>
        <p class="page-copy">
          Stokvel Society is a fintech platform for member contributions and payouts. The important thing is not simply moving money through software. It is keeping the logic legible enough for people to trust what they are seeing.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="availability-card">
        <small>Primary challenge</small>
        <strong>Financial clarity for non-technical users</strong>
        <p>The product needed to feel calm and understandable while still reflecting serious accounting and trust responsibilities underneath.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="page-section">
    <div class="container detail-layout">
      <div class="diagram-panel">
        <div class="diagram-frame">
          <img src="/images/diagram-system/stokvel-society-dashboard.png" alt="Stokvel Society wallet dashboard showing contributions, verified ledger activity, and payout visibility." />
        </div>
        <p class="diagram-caption">The flow is intentionally direct. Contributions move into a ledger layer and the payout path stays understandable.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="info-stack">
        <div class="panel">
          <div class="panel-title">What I focused on</div>
          <ul class="bullet-list">
            <li>Contribution tracking that stays visible across each cycle.</li>
            <li>Payout logic that can be explained clearly to members and administrators.</li>
            <li>Product language and UX that support trust instead of hiding behind finance jargon.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="page-section">
    <div class="container principle-grid">
      <article class="principle">
        <strong>Why it matters</strong>
        <p>Community finance works only if the product feels dependable. The interface has to support that trust, not undermine it.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="principle">
        <strong>Where the value sits</strong>
        <p>Clear contributions, visible records, and predictable payouts are worth more than visual tricks or unnecessary feature bloat.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="principle">
        <strong>What this can extend into</strong>
        <p>The same design logic applies to other trust-heavy financial products where state, accountability, and clarity matter.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
